ce:section.ce:para:
Two types of CA membranes with and without CQDs were prepared by the CA casting solutions dissolved in different solvents. The SEM images of Fig. 1
                         depict the morphology of the fabricated CA membranes with/without CQDs in different solvent systems. CA/NMP, CA/DMAc, and CA/DMSO membranes had distinct pores on the membrane surface, while the CA/2P membrane had no pores. It can be observed from Table 1 that when CA is dissolved in 2P, its solution has very high viscosity compared with other solvents. A polymer solution with high viscosity would slow down the inflow of non-solvent into casting film during wet phase inversion process, resulting in denser and low surface porosity (Table 2
                        ) [21,22]. Thus, the CA/2P membrane had a low surface porosity of about 0.02%. The cross-sectional images of the membrane shown in Fig. 1 also depict that the CA/NMP, CA/DMAc and CA/DMSO membranes have typical macrovoids morphology. It means that fast phase separation might be occurred in these three CA/solvent systems [10].
